{
  "texts": [
    "Throughout this work, superscript \"(t) \" entails that the corre- sponding symbol applies to training iteration t.",
    "Some models may be trained on data other than full training set D, e.g., subset D ⧵ z i.",
    "Let D ⊂ D denote an alternate training set, and denote model parameters trained on D as (t) D.",
    "For example, (T) D ⧵z i are the final parameters for a model trained on all of D except training instance z i ∈ D.",
    "When training on all of the training data, subscript D is dropped, i.e., (t) ≡ (t) D."
  ]
}